  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to determine which surgical approach is better for treatment of
      tibial shaft fracture
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Tibial fracture is more common fracture. We aimed to compare unreamed intramedullary nailing
      (UTN) and dynamic compression plate (DCP) with regard to fracture healing and complications
      in patients with closed tibial shaft fractures.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
